# Patch for CVE-2026-29786
# Fix path traversal via drive-relative hardlink targets in node-tar
#
# tar can be tricked into creating a hardlink pointing outside the extraction
# directory by using drive-relative link targets such as C:../target.txt.
# The root cause is that stripAbsolutePath() is called AFTER the parts.includes('..')
# check in STRIPABSOLUTEPATH, so the drive letter root is still present when the
# '..' segments are evaluated, allowing the check to be bypassed.
#
# Fix: call stripAbsolutePath() BEFORE splitting into parts so the root is
# removed first and the '..' sanitization sees only the relative remainder.
# The redundant strip call at the end of the method is removed.
# Type declaration updated to reflect the [string, string] tuple return type.
#
# This hook applies the same change as upstream commit
# 7bc755dd85e623c0279e08eb3784909e6d7e4b9f to dist/ only (7.5.7 is published
# with prebuilt dist). Apply after CVE-2026-26960. Patch applier order is
# lexicographic by CVE directory name: CVE-2026-26960, then CVE-2026-29786,
# then CVE-2026-31802, so this patch must use the post-26960 "const parts =
# p.split('/')" hunk, not a post-31802 hunk.
#
# Advisory: https://github.com/isaacs/node-tar/security/advisories/GHSA-qffp-2rhf-9h96
# NVD: https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2026-29786
# Upstream commit: https://github.com/isaacs/node-tar/commit/7bc755dd85e623c0279e08eb3784909e6d7e4b9f
# Upstream fix version: 7.5.10

